VANDALS have been slammed after a park was wrecked just after it had been renovated. Vandals wreck park VANDALS have been slammed after a park was wrecked just after it had been renovated.Benches and tables in Kelburn Park, Port Glasgow, were set on fire and damaged just weeks after a &pound;5000 refurbishment had been completed.Inverclyde's Environment &amp; Regeneration Convener, Councillor Michael McCormick, condemned the act, as resources are scarce, and called it inconsiderate and anti-social. 